Build Model and Measure Performance

In [7]:
def knn_chest_xray(dist_measure):
    # Initialize the list
    K = []
    train_accuracy = []
    test_accuracy = []

    for k in tqdm(range(1, 21), desc = 'Model train and getting outout'):
        # Initialize the classifier (clf) with the k neighbors 
        clf = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors = k, metric = dist_measure)
        # Fit the model
        clf.fit(X_train, y_train)

        training_score = clf.score(X_train, y_train)
        test_score = clf.score(X_test, y_test)
        K.append(k)

        train_accuracy.append(training_score)
        test_accuracy.append(test_score)
    
    best_k = np.argmax(test_accuracy)
    best_accuracy = np.max(test_accuracy)
    
    # Predicted class for best model
    clf = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors = best_k, metric = dist_measure)
    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test)
    return (best_k, best_accuracy, [train_accuracy, test_accuracy], y_pred)

Image Size: (32x32)

In [8]:
# Read the train data
n_train = len(train_path_normal+train_path_pneumonia)
paths_train = train_path_normal+train_path_pneumonia
X_train = np.zeros((n_train, 32*32))
for i in tqdm(range(n_train), desc = 'Read train images'):
    img = cv2.imread(paths_train[i], cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
    img_resize = cv2.resize(img, (32, 32), interpolation = cv2.INTER_AREA)
    X_train[i] = img_resize.flatten()
# Read the test data
n_test = len(test_path_normal+test_path_pneumonia)
paths_test = test_path_normal+test_path_pneumonia
X_test = np.zeros((n_test, 32*32))
for i in tqdm(range(n_test), desc = 'Read train images'):
    img = cv2.imread(paths_test[i], cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
    img_resize = cv2.resize(img, (32, 32), interpolation = cv2.INTER_AREA)
    X_test[i] = img_resize.flatten()

In [10]:
best_k, best_accuracy, accuracy, y_pred = knn_chest_xray('minkowski')

print('Best value of k is {}'.format(best_k))
print('Best test accuracy is {}%'.format(np.round(best_accuracy*100,2)))

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,4, figsize = (30,5))
ax[0].plot(accuracy[0]); ax[0].set_title('Training'); ax[0].set_xlabel('Number of neighbors (k)'); ax[0].set_ylabel('Accuracy')
ax[1].plot(accuracy[1]);  ax[1].set_title('Testing');  ax[1].set_xlabel('Number of neighbors (k)'); ax[1].set_ylabel('Accuracy')
ax[2].plot(accuracy[0]); ax[2].plot(accuracy[1]); ax[2].legend(['train','test']); ax[2].set_title('Both Together'); ax[2].set_xlabel('Number of neighbors (k)'); ax[0].set_ylabel('Accuracy')
sns.heatmap(pd.crosstab(y_test, y_pred, rownames = ['True Label'], colnames = ['Predicted Label']), annot = True, fmt = '.0f', cbar = False); ax[3].set_title('Confusion Matrix');

Best value of k is 1
Best test accuracy is 86.38%
